# harness-pm

> Personal **product management** framework · Agent must-read (the only mandatory entry point)
>
> **Positioning**: focuses solely on "doing the right things" — product discovery, market analysis, PRD generation, metrics operations, growth monitoring.
> Engineering development / UI design are handled by other harness family members, handed off via `docs/handoff/`.

## Core rules (Agent must-read; can start working without reading other files)

1. **Discovery First** — do not assume user needs; when requirements are ambiguous, research first then decide; no decisions without data
2. **Contract-Driven** — PRD drives design, positioning drives brand, event tracking drives data; key outputs are downstream contracts
3. **Data-Driven** — use data to reduce guessing; AI recommends, humans decide; confidence < 0.3 blocks auto-handoff
4. **Loop-First** — product work goes through a Loop (plan→research→validate), max 5 iterations, request human intervention after 10
5. **Session end (session-end)** — update `memory/progress.md`, then follow the `session-end` SKILL.md steps to archive (does not depend on bash scripts, cross-platform)

## PM principles (PM Principles)

> Corresponds to harness-solo's Karpathy engineering four principles; see `constitution.md` for details.

1. **Discovery First** — do not assume user needs; let research data speak. Cross-validate VOC and behavior data; interviews anchor hypotheses to be validated; label "exploratory conclusions" when there is no data (confidence ≤ 0.5)
2. **Contract-Driven** — PRD / positioning statement / metric system are downstream contracts; changes require change-impact analysis; must pass 4 quality gates (completeness / consistency / ambiguity elimination / traceability)
3. **Data-Driven** — use data to reduce guessing, but humans hold the decision rights. AI executes automatically; humans approve key decisions (option selection / priority / strategy direction). Degraded output must be human-confirmed before handoff
4. **Loop Iteration** — measure → monitor → iterate → feedback; the product is always evolving. Launch is not the end, it is the starting point of metrics operations; every iteration has verification and retrospective

**Confidence handoff rule**: ≥ 0.7 can be auto-handed off; 0.3-0.7 labeled `confidence: medium` for human confirmation; < 0.3 **blocks auto-handoff**.

## Loading chain (strict order; each step triggered only when needed)

1. **AGENTS.md** (this file) — must-read at startup
2. **SOUL.md + constitution.md** — read on first interaction (persona identity + project constitution)
